<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>West Virginia Caps Regular Season with Double Meet Weekend</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/12/gymnastics-west-virginia-caps-regular-season-with-double-meet-weekend</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/12/gymnastics-west-virginia-caps-regular-season-with-double-meet-weekend</guid><category>Gymnastics</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="amber lowe" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/12/VVB07181.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University gymnastics team is set for its final weekend of the regular season with a pair of meets on the road, beginning at No. 21 NC State on Friday, March 13. Competition inside the James T. Valvano Arena at William Neal Reynolds Coliseum in Raleigh, N.C., is set for 6 p.m. ET. The weekend then concludes in a tri meet at Pitt on Sunday, March 15. Illinois State will join the Mountaineers at the meet, which is scheduled for 2 p.m., at Fitzgerald Field House in Pittsburgh, Pa.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/12/VVB07181.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/12/VVB07181.jpg"><media:title>amber lowe</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/3/12/VVB07181.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 10:56:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>11</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58851</s:story_id></item><item><title>Hellmann Qualifies for First NCAA Swimming and Diving Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/11/mens-swimming-diving-hellmann-qualifies-for-first-ncaa-swimming-and-diving-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/11/mens-swimming-diving-hellmann-qualifies-for-first-ncaa-swimming-and-diving-championships</guid><category>Men's Swimming &amp; Diving, Women's Swimming &amp; Diving</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Levi Hellmann at 2026 Big 12 Championships (Feb. 24, 2026)" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/2/25/DSC06432.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Sophomore Levi Hellmann is heading to his first NCAA Swimming and Diving Championships after placing fourth on platform at the NCAA Zone A Diving Championships on Wednesday at Lejeune Hall in Annapolis, Maryland.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/2/25/DSC06432.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/2/25/DSC06432.jpg"><media:title>Levi Hellmann at 2026 Big 12 Championships (Feb. 24, 2026)</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/2/25/DSC06432.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 17:11:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>7</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58848</s:story_id></item><item><title>NCAA Releases Brackets for 2026 NCAA Wrestling Championships</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/11/ncaa-releases-brackets-for-2026-ncaa-wrestling-championships</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/11/ncaa-releases-brackets-for-2026-ncaa-wrestling-championships</guid><category>Wrestling</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="No alternative text provided." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2025/10/14/flynn-tim_4.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The brackets for the 2026 NCAA Wrestling Championships have been released, setting the stage for the tournament that begins on March 19 at Rocket Arena in Cleveland, Ohio.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2025/10/14/flynn-tim_4.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/10/14/flynn-tim_4.jpg"><media:title /></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2025/10/14/flynn-tim_4.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 11 Mar 2026 20:55:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>18</s:sport_id><s:story_id>58849</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Fall to BYU in Big 12 Tournament Second-Round Action</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/11/mens-basketball-mountaineers-fall-to-byu-in-big-12-tournament-second-round-action</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/3/11/mens-basketball-mountaineers-fall-to-byu-in-big-12-tournament-second-round-action</guid><category>Men's Basketball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Honor Huff" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/3/11/Huff-Main.jpg" /><br /><br />West Virginia won the battle of tempos, but BYU won the game as the Cougars defeated West Virginia 68-48 in the second night